# Component Guidelines

## Component Philosophy
- Build a library of **reusable, composable** components.
- Each component should do one thing well.
- Props should be well‑typed and documented.

## Must‑Have UI Components
- `Button` – with variants (primary, secondary, outline, ghost) and sizes.
- `Input` – text, email, password, with label and error message.
- `Card` – container with consistent padding, border, shadow.
- `Modal` – accessible dialog with header, body, footer.
- `DataTable` – sortable, filterable, paginated table.
- `DashboardWidget` – card that displays a metric or chart.
- `Avatar` – user avatar with fallback.
- `DropdownMenu` – accessible dropdown.
- `Tabs` – for switching between views.
- `Toast` – for notifications.
/components
/ui # purely presentational, reusable components
/layout # layout components (Header, Footer, Sidebar)
/forms # form-specific components
/dashboard # dashboard-specific widgets
/shared # components used across features

## Implementation Rules
- Use `"use client"` only when necessary (interactivity, hooks).
- Prefer composition over props explosion.
- Use `cn()` utility (from `clsx`/`tailwind-merge`) for conditional Tailwind classes.
- All components must have proper TypeScript types.

